{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4 below shows the trade-off between balanced accuracy and equalised odds difference.",
    "The fairness-unaware model performed best but had a relatively high equalised odds difference (i.e.",
    "could be perceived as relatively unfair).",
    "However, by performing a grid search, we identified a marginally less accurate model but one that is algorithmically fairer (see Dolata et al. (2021) for a discussion on algorithmic fairness).",
    "In comparison, the model Most fairness libraries are targeted at classification tasks, and as such, it could be challenging to apply these tools to actuarial regression problems, because the criteria are designed such that differences in a classifier's output are minimised across protected groups."
  ]
}